{"type":"item.started","item":{"id":"item_43","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"cat > code/README.md << 'EOF'\n# Computational Tools\n\n## Tool 1: SymPy\n- URL: https://www.sympy.org/\n- Purpose: Symbolic algebra support for equation manipulation, normal forms, and small-scale sanity checks.\n- Location: Python package in local \"'`.venv`\n- Key usage for this project: prototype rewrite systems and verify algebraic equalities in specific interpreted models.\n\n## Tool 2: Mace4 (reference manual)\n- URL: https://arxiv.org/abs/cs/0310055\n- Purpose: Finite model search for first-order/equational formulas, useful for finding countermodels to non-implications.\n- Location: manual PDF at `papers/cs_0310055_mace4_manual.pdf`\n- Notes: binary not bundled in this workspace; manual documents input language and search controls.\n\n## Tool 3: Paper chunker workflow\n- URL: local script `.claude/skills/paper-finder/scripts/pdf_chunker.py`\n- Purpose: Split PDFs into page chunks for structured reading and theorem extraction.\n- Location: local repo tooling\n- Notes: all chunk outputs stored under `papers/pages/`.\n\n## Installed Python Packages\n- `pypdf`, `requests`, `arxiv`, `httpx`, `sympy`\n\n## Applicability to Current Hypothesis\n- For implication checking `E1 => E2` over magmas, finite-model search can quickly refute false implications.\n- For true implications, theorem provers with learned guidance (as in the reviewed papers) are the main direction.\nEOF'","aggregated_output":"","exit_code":null,"status":"in_progress"}}
